= Simulation Component =

A `Simulation` defines a computational astrophysics [NotesComponentProblem Problem] as initialized from `Parameters`.  [NotesComponentControl Control] is used to initialize the simulation and run it.


  || `Simulation()` || || 
  ||  `~Simulation()` || || 
  || `initialize()` || ''Initialize the Simulation given input parameters'' ||
  || || ||
  || `dimension()` ||  ''Return the dimensionality of the problem'' || 
  || `domain_extents()` ||  ''Return the lower and upper extents of the domain'' || 
  || || ||
  || `num_fields()` || ''Return the number of fields'' ||
  || `field()` || ''Return the nth field '' ||
  || `num_methods()` || ''Return the number of methods'' ||
  || `method()` || ''Return the nth method '' ||
  || `parallel()` || ''Return the `Parallel` object'' ||
  || `mesh()` || ''Return the `Mesh` object'' ||

 